  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether remote ischemic conditioning can improve
      the outcome after renal transplantation with deceased donor. Remote ischemic conditioning is
      performed on the patient receiving a kidney from a deceased donor. Remote ischemic
      conditioning is done during the operation by inflating a tourniquet on the patients leg
      before opening the blood circulation to the kidney. The study focus on both the immediate
      kidney function after the transplantation, but also on the extended kidney function one year
      after the transplantation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
